Name: OLI_GOVTID_AGEOFMAJ
Definition: Proof-of-age identification for purchasing alcoholic beverages.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_CANBN
Definition: This is the business number assigned to an corporation by the Canadian Government

Name: OLI_GOVTID_CANEIN
Definition: The Employer ID Number assigned to an corporation by the Canadian Government

Name: OLI_GOVTID_CANNEQ
Definition: This is the enterprise number assigned to an corporation by the Canadian Quebec Government

Name: OLI_GOVTID_INDSTAT
Definition: First issued in 1956, the Certificate of Indian Status, more commonly referred to as a Status card, is an identity document issued for administrative reasons by Aboriginal Affairs and Northern Development Canada (AANDC) to confirm that the cardholder is registered as a Status Indian under the Indian Act.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_CHINAMIL
Definition: China began a residential identity card system in 1985 which ruled that servicemen and armed police had separate military or armed police cards instead of civilian identity cards. A Law on Resident Identity Cards which came into effect in 2004 for the first time enlarged the card issuance scope to servicemen and armed police. OLI_GOVTID_CHINAMIL represents this card.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_CITIZENSHIPID
Definition: A generic ID from a foreign country. The country may or may not be known.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_GIIN
Definition: Global Intermediary Identification Number

Name: OLI_GOVTID_GREENCARD
Definition: Indicates the GovtID is a US issued "Green Card" (INS Alien Registration Receipt Card) Number or Identifier which is issued as proof of permanent residency for a non-US citizen living in the US.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_IDNUM
Definition: Identification Number used to uniquely identify a person in a country.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_MEDICAIDNUM
Definition: The number entered is a Medicaid Number in the United States.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_MBI
Definition: The Medicare Beneficiary Identifier (MBI) replaces the Social Security number (SSN) on Medicare cards for Medicare transactions such as billing, eligibility status, and claim status.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_MEDICARENUM
Definition: The number entered is a Medicare Number in the United States.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_NPI
Definition: A National Provider Identifier or NPI is a unique 10-digit identification number issued to health care providers in the United States by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services

Name: OLI_GOVTID_OLDAGEID
Definition: The Old Age Security (OAS) Identification Card used to be sent out to seniors, who reached age 65 and have lived in Canada for at least 10 years. While no longer issued, it is still valid if previously obtained; and it may be previously captured/stored as part of client's historical record on inforce policies.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_PASSPORTID
Definition: Indicates the GovtID is a Passport Number or Identifier.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_PHOTOID
Definition: Photo ID Card issued by a provincial, state, or territorial government.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_RRMEDICARENBR
Definition: The number, generally the employee's Social Security Number with a prefix which describes familial relationship, used by the Railroad Retirement Board to identify an individual who has retired from a Railroad and who is now receiving Medicare benefits.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_RAILROADRETIREENBR
Definition: The number, generally the employee's Social Security Number, used by the Railroad Retirement Board to identify an individual who is or has worked for a Railroad.

Name: OLI_GOVTID_RECORDOFLAND
Definition: Provided at time of entry representing legal entry into the country.

Description: Tax ID for US non-resident alien
Name: OLI_GOVTID_USNONRESTID
OLI_GOVTID_TID
Definition: Taxpayer Identification Number (TIN) is a generic term that can be used to describe any form of tax id (e. g. Social Security Number for people, US Employer Identification Number for organizations).
